      • rowCursor

        default Stream<IndexPair> rowCursor()
        Returns a cursor which traverses the table by its rows. For example, a 3x3 table will be traversed in this order: 
         |0|1|2|
 |-|-|-|
 |3|4|5|
 |6|7|8|
        Or, in IndexPair's: 
         [0|0], [1|0], [2|0], [0|1], [1|1], [2|1], [0|2], [1|2], [2|2]

      • rowCursor

        default Stream<IndexPair> rowCursor​(BiPredicate<Integer,Integer> pred)
        Shorthand for rowCursor().filter(idx -> pred.test(idx.getColumn(), idx.getRow())) .
        See Also:
        rowCursor()

      • columnCursor

        default Stream<IndexPair> columnCursor()
        Returns a cursor which traverses the table by its columns. For example, a 3x3 table will be traversed in this order: 
         |0|3|6|
 |-|-|-|
 |1|4|7|
 |2|5|8|
        Or, in IndexPair's: 
         [0|0], [0|1], [0|2], [1|0], [1|1], [2|2], [2|0], [2|1], [2|2]

      • columnCursor
